{c_label}Character Level{/c} 
Click to open the Character screen.
Crackling Energy periodically damages nearby enemies when picked up.
Display floating numbers above monsters that show normal damage dealt by the player.
Display floating numbers above monsters that show Critical Strike Damage dealt by the player.
Display floating numbers above monsters that show Blocks, Parries, and Dodges.
Briefly display item tooltips when the item drops on the ground.
Display health bars for damaged monsters.
Display health bars for damaged enemy players.
Prevents the user from picking up or dragging Skills onto the action bar. Hold down the SHIFT key to move Skills when the action bar is locked.
Display names and health bars over friendly players.
Use Environmental Audio Extensions for more realistic sounds.
Swap the output of your left and right speakers.
Synchronizes your frame rate to some fraction of your monitor's refresh rate. This will reduce tearing of the image.
Triple buffering can improve the smoothness of your frame rate.
Enable depth of field. (Only recommended for high-end systems.)
Higher resolution will result in increased clarity, but this greatly affects performance. Choose a resolution that matches the aspect ratio of your monitor.
Determines the clarity and size of textures used throughout the game. Higher texture quality will result in more detail, but it requires more video memory.

Determines the realism of colliding objects and gravity.

Physics relies on your computer's processor (CPU).
Higher quality reflections may require a more powerful system.
Fullscreen Anti-Aliasing can smooth the image and eliminate jagged edges.
Displays a translucent overlay window with a history of the player's chat messages and console commands.
Opens a one-line box for typing chat messages or console commands.
Slides the console window down from the top of the screen, and lets the player issue game commands.
Press this key to toggle auto-run mode, which will allow you to move without holding down a mouse button. You can cancel auto-run by pressing this key again or pressing any mouse button.
Press this key to change the default movement from walking to running.

Allows you to change the primary display mode of the game to Fullscreen, Windowed, or Windowed (Fullscreen). Windowed modes may cause a drop in performance.
